The paper discusses a prototype of a semantic wiki that uses controlled natural language (Attempto Controlled English) to make ontology management easy for everyone. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves natural language processing and knowledge representation. Additionally, the paper mentions the integration of an OWL reasoner (Pellet) for consistency checking, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The use of natural language also suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions previous results showing that people with no background in logic can add formal knowledge to the wiki, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of user interface design and usability testing.
